I"<p>I purchased a
<a href="https://www.tp-link.com/au/home-networking/powerline/tl-wpa4220/">TL-WPA4220</a>
which turns out to be unreliable, with the connection not staying up more than
a day or so.</p>

<!-- more -->

<p>Firmware version: 4.0.3 Build 20190326 Rel.43406 
<br />
Hardware version: TL-WPA4220 v4.0</p>

<p>After a bit of browsing I found this <a href="https://community.tp-link.com/en/home/forum/topic/78910">https://community.tp-link.com/en/home/forum/topic/78910</a>. I added
this script on the Ubuntu Linux machine at the other end of the powerline adaptor</p>

<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>while true
do
	date
	ping -c 1 192.168.0.1
	sleep 60
done
</code></pre></div></div>
<p>and the problem has gone away.</p>

:ET